<title>USA: Software Artistry ends share repurchase.</title>
<headline>Software Artistry ends share repurchase.</headline>
<dateline>INDIANAPOLIS 1997-01-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Software Artistry Inc said Tuesday it has discontinued a share repurchase program, after buying back only 242,500 of the 500,000 shares authorized.</p>
<p>&quot;We felt that it was in the best interest of our shareholders to conserve our capital for other needs,&quot; chief financial officer Thomas Vanneman said in an interview. Those needs include product expansion and acquisitions, he said.  </p>
<p>The software company has targeted the market between companies and customers for expansion in 1997, he said.</p>
<p>The stock repurchase plan was authorized in January 1996.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk 312 408 8787))</p>
